### 🎯 SUCCESS CRITERIA:

**AI declares success ONLY when**:
- ✅ Specification exists and validated (10/10 from all models)
- ✅ BMAD record created with complete traceability
- ✅ Tests written FIRST and initially failing (RED phase)
- ✅ Implementation makes tests pass (GREEN phase)
- ✅ Code refactored and optimized (REFACTOR phase)
- ✅ Implementation validated (10/10 from all models)
- ✅ All compliance requirements met
- ✅ Deployment artifacts created
- ✅ Production self-validation enabled

### ❌ COMMON MISTAKES AI MUST PREVENT:

1. ❌ Writing code before specification
2. ❌ Writing code before tests
3. ❌ Accepting < 10/10 validation scores
4. ❌ Skipping HIPAA compliance checks
5. ❌ Missing PHI/PII access logging
6. ❌ Incomplete error handling
7. ❌ Missing type hints
8. ❌ Missing docstrings
9. ❌ Hardcoded configuration values
10. ❌ Missing audit trail implementation

### 📞 ESCALATION:

**AI MUST escalate to human when**:
- 5 iterations completed without achieving 10/10
- Specification requirements unclear after questions
- Safety-critical decision needed
- Regulatory interpretation required
- Architectural decision with major impact

